description:
Job Responsibilities:

Handle full set of shipping arrangement for import/export include getting freight quotation, PO processing, Packing List, Export Declaration documents e,g. Certificate of Origin (worldwide) and large volume of data entry;
Work of the preparation, submission, recording & filing of import/export shipping documents;
Prepare daily & monthly Logistics & Inventory report;
Well communication skills with forwarders;
Provide support to ad hoc tasks as assigned.

Requirements:

Form 5 or DSE graduate;
Minimum 3-4 years in related working experience;
Knowledge & experience in import/export procedures and custom declaration regulations including CEPA & TradeLink application;
Factory of plastic field experience is an advantage;
Familiar with EXCEL and MS Office;
Team player, pro-active, willing to meet challenge and learn attitude;
Good command in spoken and written English, Chinese and Mandarin;
Immediate available would be highly preferred.

 We offer 5-day work with attractive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.

 Please send your full resume with availability, current & expected salary to HR Department:

Responsibilities:


Order process and upload PO into MIS system;
Follow up and ensure shipping schedule to meet the department target;
Prepare full set of order processing and shipment report;
Assist buying team on order status and coordinate with the sales team on the delivery requests;
Communicate with the internal department for arranging order instruction/payment request form and coordinating with the overseas vendors for the shipment schedule;
Monitor the order processing with the operation and ensure shipment on schedule;
Establish a good leadership with the internal team and well relationship with the internal department for the day to day operation and reporting
Review operation regularly and recommend improvement and action plan
Supervise team members to support daily distribution/operations.

Requirements: 


Bachelor Degree/ High Diploma in Logistics, Supply Chain Management, or a related disciplines;
Minimum 3 years experience in order processing field;
Energetic, motivated, full of initiative, shipping and logistics' knowledge is required and able to work independently and under pressure;

Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (e.g. Excel is a must);
Good command of interpersonal and communication skills;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Logistics Supervisor. 
We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.  Please apply in strict confidence by sending personal resume together with salary expected and date available

by email to: h r d _ h n @ h a r v e y n i c h o l s . c o m . h k
