Responsibilities:

Liaise and coordinate order processing with various parties internally and externally, including: shipping team, buyers, warehouse team, finance team and vendors;
Monitor and update shipment order status;
Process the purchase order in accordance with MIS system and monitor the shipment lead time;
Prepare and follow up internal documentation forms.

Requirements: 

Post-secondary or Diploma;
Independent, hard-working and honest;
Good command of Microsoft Excel, Word and Power Point;
Fluent in English and Chinese;
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

We offer excellent career prospects, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.  Please apply in strict confidence by sending personal resume together with salary expected and date available:

 by email to: h r d _ h n @ h a r v e y n i c h o l s . c o m . h k

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within eight weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months. A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request by contacting our Human Resources Division.

Responsibilities




Provide clerical support to daily sales activities, including preparation of issuing purchase order, sales quotation, sales contract, invoices, and perform goods receipt in ERP system;
Handle full set of banking documents, I/E documents, L/C opening and eRO system;
Coordinate with logistics department, warehouses, customers and concerned parties for goods delivery;
Liaise with accounting department to maintain up-to-date customer database & prepare month-end reports;
Well support for sales coordination with both internal and external parties;
Ad-hoc duties as assigned

Requirements


Higher Diploma graduated or above with 3 years solid working experience in  shipping and trading firm preferred;

Good knowledge of customs procedures in Hong Kong & PRC are preferable;
Experience in SAP / ERP system is an advantage;
Proficiency in MS Word, Excel and Chinese Word Processing;
Good command of spoken & written English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Able to work independent and self-motivated;
Well organizational and interpersonal communication skills

Interested candidates please send your application with full resume, present and expected salary in confidence to our Ms. Elaine Tang, Jacobson van den Berg (Hong Kong) Ltd, Flat A, 7/F., Cheung Lung Industrial Building, 10 Cheung Yee Street, Cheung Sha Wan, Kln., H.K. or by email.

