Job Responsibilities:

1. Responsible for overseas collaborative marketing and promotion, comprehensively promote and promote collaborative business within the establish effective contacts, and explore potential projects;

2. Responsible for the operation and management of the collaborative project, including designing the project plan, analyzing the project risk, cost estimation, fee quotation, contract negotiation according to the potential business; initiating project settlement, operation tracking, collection of accounts receivable, project feedback, and internal and external customers of the system Supplier maintenance;

3. Responsible for the summary work of overseas collaborative projects;

4. Responsible for the specific implementation of overseas collaborative projects;

5. Responsible for completing the temporary work of the department.

Job Requirements:

1. Bachelor degree or above, no major limitation, logistics, trade and other related majors are preferred;

2. Working experience in shipping, logistics and settlement is preferred;

3. Work proactive, serious and meticulous, good communication skills and teamwork spirit;

4. Recognize Chinese Company culture.

Responsibilities:
Assist to handle full sets of accounts and related financial accounting duties
Perform general accounting duties include AP, AR, prepare vouchers and data entry
Handle and verify petty cash transactions
Participate in physical stock take at the end of every month
Assist in preparing month end closing, auditing and taxation affairs
Other ad-hoc assignments
Requirement:
Form 5, DSE or above with LCCI higher qualification;
Minimum 1-2 years in accounting;
Details minded; Multi-tasking and capable to manage tight schedule;
Self-initiated with can-do attitude;
Well-knowledge in using Microsoft Word & Excel;
Strong communication and interpersonal skills;
Effective written and verbal communication skills;
Fair command of English and Mandarin;
Benefits:
5 days work
Annual Leave  11 days
Birthday Leave
Anniversary Leave
Year End Bonus
Interested candidates should send a detailed Resume, including expected salary, to "Human Resources Manager, Wing Kee Produce Limited. G/F Hong Leong Ind. Complex, 4 Wang Kwong Road, Kowloon Bay, Kowloon, Hong Kong" Email by clicking  "Apply Now"
